With JDK 7 there is a bug exporting plugins from Eclipse > 4.x 
See https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=371215


This is the error: 

>>>>>>>>>>>

/Users/Christophe/Documents/Spaces/netxstudio/.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.pde.core/temp/org.eclipse.pde.container.feature/compile.org.eclipse.pde.container.feature.xml:4: The following error occurred while executing this line:
/Users/Christophe/Documents/Projects/GIT_netxstudio/3rdPartyLib/org.apache.poi/build.xml:31: /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.7.0_07.jdk/Contents/Home/Classes does not exist.
The following error occurred while executing this line:
/Users/Christophe/Documents/Projects/GIT_netxstudio/3rdPartyLib/org.apache.poi/build.xml:31: /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.7.0_07.jdk/Contents/Home/Classes does not exist.

>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>


To get around: 

/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.7[version].jdk/Contents/Home.


